1
00:01:33,760 --> 00:01:34,880
Come on, have some skewers.

2
00:01:36,400 --> 00:01:38,160
Can you really finish all this?

3
00:01:38,320 --> 00:01:39,680
These are just appetizers.

4
00:01:39,680 --> 00:01:40,680
There's big squid coming later.

5
00:01:40,960 --> 00:01:41,520
Give it a try.

6
00:01:42,800 --> 00:01:44,200
Not bad, you.

7
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:47,280
You really taught Xiao Min a lesson.

8
00:01:47,280 --> 00:01:49,240
But your deal with Xuan Yan isn't settled yet.

9
00:01:49,920 --> 00:01:51,440
With those shameless little tricks of his,

10
00:01:51,720 --> 00:01:53,000
how could I ever fall for them?

11
00:01:54,080 --> 00:01:56,000
But somehow I get the feeling

12
00:01:56,440 --> 00:01:58,440
that Xuan Yan is hitting on you.

13
00:01:59,960 --> 00:02:00,800
Hitting on me?

14
00:02:01,920 --> 00:02:03,120
Oh, give me a break.

15
00:02:14,160 --> 00:02:14,960
Chairman Xiao.

16
00:02:15,360 --> 00:02:16,240
Comrade Xiao Lin.

17
00:02:16,920 --> 00:02:18,000
I'm really sorry.

18
00:02:18,080 --> 00:02:19,160
I was just joking with you guys.

19
00:02:19,160 --> 00:02:20,280
Don't take it to heart.

20
00:02:20,680 --> 00:02:21,480
It's fine.

21
00:02:22,040 --> 00:02:23,400
What you said earlier today,

22
00:02:23,400 --> 00:02:24,520
you only said half and ran off.

23
00:02:24,520 --> 00:02:27,400
Leaving the other half as a riddle for me?

24
00:02:27,520 --> 00:02:29,400
Chairman Xiao, I think for this matter,

25
00:02:29,520 --> 00:02:31,840
you obviously know Xuan Yan said it, right?

26
00:02:31,840 --> 00:02:33,040
You can just ask him directly.

27
00:02:34,080 --> 00:02:34,920
I did ask him.

28
00:02:34,920 --> 00:02:36,000
He told me to ask you.

29
00:02:36,200 --> 00:02:37,080
Where are you?

30
00:02:37,160 --> 00:02:39,000
You didn't get a proper meal today.

31
00:02:39,200 --> 00:02:40,440
Let me treat you to dinner.

32
00:02:42,560 --> 00:02:43,920
It's a bit late tonight.

33
00:02:43,920 --> 00:02:45,080
I think we should skip dinner.

34
00:02:45,080 --> 00:02:48,200
How about we meet at the Economic Office tomorrow?

35
00:02:48,720 --> 00:02:49,480
Tomorrow afternoon won't work.

36
00:02:49,480 --> 00:02:50,200
I'm busy.

37
00:02:50,200 --> 00:02:51,440
How about tomorrow morning instead?

38
00:02:51,440 --> 00:02:53,560
If that works, I'll come find you first thing.

39
00:02:53,920 --> 00:02:54,560
Sure.

40
00:02:54,560 --> 00:02:55,320
That works.

41
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:02,640
Chairman Xiao.

42
00:03:03,360 --> 00:03:03,840
Don't rush off.

43
00:03:03,840 --> 00:03:04,720
Come in and wait.

44
00:03:05,080 --> 00:03:05,720
Where's Lin Yiran?

45
00:03:05,920 --> 00:03:07,360
I've been waiting all morning.

46
00:03:07,360 --> 00:03:08,080
She won't answer calls.

47
00:03:08,080 --> 00:03:08,640
She won't reply to messages.

48
00:03:08,640 --> 00:03:09,280
She even hung up on me.

49
00:03:09,280 --> 00:03:10,200
What's that supposed to mean?

50
00:03:10,200 --> 00:03:11,280
Where on earth is she?

51
00:03:26,200 --> 00:03:27,440
How did you find this place?

52
00:03:30,200 --> 00:03:31,720
Auntie Xu told me.

53
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:32,800
What's up?

54
00:03:33,360 --> 00:03:34,200
Something going on?

55
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:38,200
I came specifically to thank you.

56
00:03:47,120 --> 00:03:48,120
Are you here to thank me,

57
00:03:48,120 --> 00:03:49,520
or to make a fool of me?

58
00:03:50,560 --> 00:03:51,440
What a thing to say.

59
00:03:51,440 --> 00:03:53,200
How could I possibly mess with you?

60
00:03:54,360 --> 00:03:56,320
But there's something I do need to discuss.

61
00:04:02,360 --> 00:04:02,880
You see, I am,

62
00:04:02,880 --> 00:04:04,000
after all, a civil servant.

63
00:04:04,720 --> 00:04:06,120
I really do have to mind

64
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:07,480
the image of a civil servant, right?

65
00:04:07,680 --> 00:04:09,880
Could we swap that favor for something else?

66
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:11,520
Or you could put it on hold,

67
00:04:11,920 --> 00:04:14,200
and I'll repay you when the chance comes.

68
00:04:14,640 --> 00:04:15,240
Okay?

69
00:04:20,600 --> 00:04:21,640
The deal's off.

70
00:04:25,920 --> 00:04:26,960
I don't need it.

71
00:04:28,960 --> 00:04:31,320
Otherwise, how about another condition?

72
00:04:32,680 --> 00:04:36,040
There was once a fair deal

73
00:04:36,040 --> 00:04:37,320
right in front of you,

74
00:04:37,320 --> 00:04:38,880
and you didn't cherish it.

75
00:04:39,200 --> 00:04:41,240
Now you're full of regret.

76
00:04:41,520 --> 00:04:43,080
I'm afraid even if I gave you another chance,

77
00:04:44,120 --> 00:04:45,080
you'd just blow it.

78
00:04:57,080 --> 00:04:57,880
What are you doing?

79
00:04:58,600 --> 00:04:59,800
Are you clinging to me now?

80
00:05:07,400 --> 00:05:08,360
Comrade Xiao Lin.

81
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:11,320
You've had quite a busy morning.

82
00:05:11,920 --> 00:05:13,200
I'm waiting for you at the office.

83
00:05:13,200 --> 00:05:14,240
When are you coming back?

84
00:05:15,160 --> 00:05:15,880
Chairman Xiao.

85
00:05:15,880 --> 00:05:17,240
I'm with Xuan Yan right now.

86
00:05:17,240 --> 00:05:18,360
I think there are some things

87
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:19,600
the three of us should

88
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:21,680
talk through together to clear up.

89
00:05:21,680 --> 00:05:22,120
Okay, okay, okay.

90
00:05:22,120 --> 00:05:22,960
Go ahead, speak.

91
00:05:24,120 --> 00:05:24,920
First of all,

92
00:05:25,080 --> 00:05:25,920
Jiang Ziliu said

93
00:05:25,920 --> 00:05:28,400
he couldn't find a single good sheet at the Xuan family's.

94
00:05:28,400 --> 00:05:30,200
What's damaged is the Xuan family

95
00:05:30,200 --> 00:05:32,520
and the reputation of Taohua Town's Xuan paper industry.

96
00:05:32,520 --> 00:05:33,960
It has nothing to do with me.

97
00:05:34,080 --> 00:05:37,080
I followed Secretary Peng's orders to hold the Paper King Contest.

98
00:05:37,120 --> 00:05:38,920
It was also to help your Xuan family

99
00:05:38,920 --> 00:05:40,520
and Taohua Town's Xuan paper industry.

100
00:05:42,680 --> 00:05:43,520
And another thing,

101
00:05:43,640 --> 00:05:45,520
whether you take responsibility isn't my concern.

102
00:05:45,520 --> 00:05:46,800
I can quit this job.

103
00:05:46,800 --> 00:05:48,320
I can walk away from this project too.

104
00:05:48,320 --> 00:05:49,200
But,

105
00:05:49,440 --> 00:05:51,600
if you use the contest venue issue

106
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:52,880
to threaten me,

107
00:05:52,880 --> 00:05:55,000
I'll only find you shameless.

108
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:55,760
Ridiculous.

109
00:05:55,920 --> 00:05:56,720
And childish.

110
00:05:58,480 --> 00:05:59,280
I-

111
00:05:59,280 --> 00:06:00,400
Hey, hey, hey.

112
00:06:03,360 --> 00:06:04,040
Lin Yiran.

113
00:06:05,520 --> 00:06:06,200
What are you doing?

114
00:06:06,680 --> 00:06:07,880
The car keys. What are you doing?

115
00:06:16,320 --> 00:06:17,240
Wait, Lin Yiran.

116
00:06:45,440 --> 00:06:46,640
We agreed on a deal.

117
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:48,880
Not honoring it isn't right, is it?

118
00:06:49,560 --> 00:06:51,680
I'm no longer interested in dealing with you.

119
00:06:52,320 --> 00:06:53,760
You're quite the cheat, aren't you?

120
00:06:54,160 --> 00:06:54,920
Thank you.

121
00:06:54,920 --> 00:06:55,880
Thanks for the compliment.

122
00:06:56,640 --> 00:06:57,800
So you're mad at me.

123
00:06:59,320 --> 00:07:01,000
Everyone who's ever been mad at me

124
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:02,000
has loved me.

125
00:07:02,240 --> 00:07:03,800
Didn't know you liked me too.

126
00:07:04,080 --> 00:07:05,800
Wait, how can you be so full of yourself?

127
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:07,320
You're the one who hinted at it.

128
00:07:07,440 --> 00:07:09,000
What hint did I ever give you?

129
00:07:09,240 --> 00:07:10,560
You staying mad at me

130
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:13,440
means you'll keep me on your mind.

131
00:07:15,440 --> 00:07:16,320
Remember this.

132
00:07:16,880 --> 00:07:18,360
You owe me a favor.

133
00:07:20,800 --> 00:07:22,240
Did I ever agree to that?

134
00:07:23,120 --> 00:07:24,640
Hey, I'm talking to you.

135
00:07:26,080 --> 00:07:27,360
You think you're the only fast driver?

136
00:07:27,680 --> 00:07:28,680
I drive fast too.

137
00:07:37,360 --> 00:07:38,320
Comrade Xiao Lin!

138
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:43,560
Comrade Xiao Lin!

139
00:07:50,680 --> 00:07:52,160
Xuan Yan, you've got some nerve.

140
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:54,960
Siding with outsiders now, huh?

141
00:07:56,200 --> 00:07:57,400
Using me, using me

142
00:07:57,400 --> 00:07:59,000
as a pawn, aren't you?

143
00:08:00,320 --> 00:08:01,200
Tell me the truth.

144
00:08:02,560 --> 00:08:04,880
What's going on between you and her?

145
00:08:05,760 --> 00:08:07,280
There's nothing going on.

146
00:08:07,480 --> 00:08:09,720
And how am I siding with outsiders?

147
00:08:09,840 --> 00:08:11,160
What I'm doing right now

148
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:13,400
is for our Taohua Town's Xuan paper businesses.

149
00:08:13,400 --> 00:08:14,960
That's just public service.

150
00:08:15,200 --> 00:08:16,760
Making yourself sound so noble.

151
00:08:17,360 --> 00:08:18,920
Don't blame me for not warning you.

152
00:08:19,320 --> 00:08:20,280
That girl?

153
00:08:21,400 --> 00:08:22,440
She's got quite a temper.

154
00:08:22,680 --> 00:08:23,880
You'd better be careful.

155
00:08:24,080 --> 00:08:26,160
Do you want to patch up that hole or not?

156
00:08:26,280 --> 00:08:27,120
The moment she said it, I knew

157
00:08:27,120 --> 00:08:28,440
it was your lousy idea.

158
00:08:28,480 --> 00:08:30,240
Spit it out, I'm busy over here.

159
00:08:30,840 --> 00:08:31,880
Back in the day,

160
00:08:32,320 --> 00:08:35,200
you betrayed our master's teachings to run a mechanical paper mill.

161
00:08:36,799 --> 00:08:38,320
Watch your words, please.

162
00:08:38,640 --> 00:08:41,320
I was heading down the road to a better life.

163
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:45,040
What do you think your master, my father,

164
00:08:45,040 --> 00:08:46,280
is most angry at you about?

165
00:08:48,680 --> 00:08:51,680
Definitely that I abandoned the craft.

166
00:08:51,760 --> 00:08:54,040
You were his most valued senior apprentice.

167
00:08:54,560 --> 00:08:55,640
You just walked away.

168
00:08:55,880 --> 00:08:57,840
Didn't that break the old man's heart?

169
00:08:58,120 --> 00:09:01,320
Naturally, he scratched you off

170
00:09:01,320 --> 00:09:02,640
the Xuan family lineage scroll.

171
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:05,600
If you enter the Paper King Contest

172
00:09:05,600 --> 00:09:06,680
and place well,

173
00:09:06,680 --> 00:09:07,960
how do you think he'll feel?

174
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:10,560
He'll see your skills aren't lost,

175
00:09:10,760 --> 00:09:11,840
that you haven't forgotten your roots.

176
00:09:14,040 --> 00:09:14,880
And then?

177
00:09:15,200 --> 00:09:16,280
Then you offer a proper apology,

178
00:09:16,280 --> 00:09:17,840
throw a big banquet, and beg his forgiveness.

179
00:09:17,840 --> 00:09:19,600
Wouldn't that patch the hole right up?

180
00:09:24,160 --> 00:09:25,680
The logic checks out,

181
00:09:26,800 --> 00:09:28,560
but I've been out of practice for so many years.

182
00:09:28,560 --> 00:09:29,520
What if I lose?

183
00:09:30,880 --> 00:09:31,960
Xiao Min,

184
00:09:32,480 --> 00:09:34,880
hard work makes up for a lack of talent.

185
00:09:38,120 --> 00:09:39,520
Yes, yes, yes, Master.

186
00:09:39,840 --> 00:09:41,160
Hard work makes up for a lack of talent.

187
00:09:41,880 --> 00:09:43,080
Alright, I'll be off then.

188
00:09:43,280 --> 00:09:43,920
Alright.

189
00:09:44,280 --> 00:09:46,160
Just don't go turning things upside down

190
00:09:46,160 --> 00:09:46,800
by taking first place.

191
00:09:46,800 --> 00:09:47,800
Forget patching it up,

192
00:09:47,800 --> 00:09:49,360
he'll rip your whole page out.

193
00:09:50,920 --> 00:09:52,040
That'll never happen.

194
00:09:52,120 --> 00:09:53,440
Master will always be number one.

195
00:09:53,560 --> 00:09:55,760
I'll aim for third, maybe fight for second.

196
00:09:55,760 --> 00:09:56,840
Hey, don't rush off.

197
00:09:57,240 --> 00:09:58,320
About the venue for the Paper King Contest,

198
00:09:58,320 --> 00:09:59,360
sort it out for me.

199
00:10:00,080 --> 00:10:00,760
No problem.

200
00:10:02,520 --> 00:10:03,280
Alright.

201
00:10:43,120 --> 00:10:44,880
There's an old saying from years past:

202
00:10:45,720 --> 00:10:47,520
"Look at the water, know the paper's fate."

203
00:10:47,880 --> 00:10:49,960
The quality of a sheet of Xuan paper

204
00:10:50,160 --> 00:10:51,640
can be judged by the color of the water,

205
00:10:51,840 --> 00:10:53,760
nine times out of ten.

206
00:10:58,520 --> 00:11:01,000
Fine Xuan paper, though thin as a cicada's wing,

207
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:02,960
can hold thick ink and heavy gold.

208
00:11:03,160 --> 00:11:04,640
Is it really just because

209
00:11:04,720 --> 00:11:05,880
of the water's quality?

210
00:11:06,280 --> 00:11:06,600
No.

211
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:07,640
Water,

212
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:08,760
pulp,

213
00:11:08,800 --> 00:11:09,600
materials,

214
00:11:09,640 --> 00:11:10,480
time,

215
00:11:10,520 --> 00:11:11,520
plus scooping,

216
00:11:11,720 --> 00:11:12,520
drying,

217
00:11:12,760 --> 00:11:13,640
trimming...

218
00:11:14,040 --> 00:11:16,360
every step of the craft is indispensable.

219
00:11:16,400 --> 00:11:17,880
Only paper forged through

220
00:11:17,880 --> 00:11:19,120
all 108 procedures

221
00:11:19,160 --> 00:11:21,640
endures the sun and lasts a thousand years.

222
00:11:34,760 --> 00:11:36,400
You want to scoop paper?

223
00:11:38,640 --> 00:11:40,000
How long has it been?

224
00:11:40,760 --> 00:11:41,520
Can you still do it?

225
00:11:42,240 --> 00:11:42,760
Master Dou,

226
00:11:44,520 --> 00:11:45,520
please help me lift the screen.

227
00:11:45,960 --> 00:11:46,520
All right.

228
00:11:56,520 --> 00:11:57,120
Master,

229
00:11:57,120 --> 00:11:58,640
my arms ache, I can't lift it.

230
00:12:00,040 --> 00:12:01,000
Think carefully.

231
00:12:02,040 --> 00:12:03,400
Is it your hands that can't lift,

232
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:04,960
or your heart?

233
00:12:07,560 --> 00:12:08,520
It's the heart.

234
00:12:09,280 --> 00:12:10,280
It's willpower.

235
00:12:11,760 --> 00:12:12,920
Xiao Min, remember this:

236
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:14,600
you have to push yourself.

237
00:12:14,840 --> 00:12:15,400
Understand?

238
00:12:16,480 --> 00:12:17,960
The world has many temptations,

239
00:12:17,960 --> 00:12:18,960
and desires grow with them.

240
00:12:19,120 --> 00:12:20,360
If your willpower isn't strong enough,

241
00:12:20,680 --> 00:12:21,760
you won't make it through.

242
00:12:22,840 --> 00:12:24,040
A lifetime is long.

243
00:12:24,640 --> 00:12:25,360
Only this way

244
00:12:25,800 --> 00:12:27,400
can you live with integrity,

245
00:12:28,840 --> 00:12:30,240
and a clear conscience.

246
00:12:30,240 --> 00:12:31,080
Got it?

247
00:12:31,960 --> 00:12:32,760
Got it.

248
00:12:42,920 --> 00:12:44,680
Move the second sign a bit to the right.

249
00:12:44,680 --> 00:12:45,600
Just a bit to the right.

250
00:12:46,560 --> 00:12:46,960
That's it.

251
00:12:46,960 --> 00:12:48,880
Third one, Zhuzhu, scoot it right too.

252
00:12:49,960 --> 00:12:50,760
You got it.

253
00:12:50,800 --> 00:12:51,760
Let me take a look.

254
00:12:51,760 --> 00:12:52,960
Good, yours is fine now.

255
00:12:54,600 --> 00:12:55,560
All set then.

256
00:12:56,960 --> 00:12:58,480
Let me check these signs.

257
00:12:58,880 --> 00:12:59,640
Everything okay?

258
00:12:59,640 --> 00:13:00,120
All good.

259
00:13:00,120 --> 00:13:01,720
Great, we'll hang them up shortly.

260
00:13:01,720 --> 00:13:02,760
Okay, sure, sure.

261
00:13:02,760 --> 00:13:03,640
Master Dou,

262
00:13:04,360 --> 00:13:05,880
check the vats in a bit,

263
00:13:05,880 --> 00:13:06,480
and the equipment too.

264
00:13:06,480 --> 00:13:07,880
Let me know if it's all good.

265
00:13:07,880 --> 00:13:08,480
All right.

266
00:13:08,480 --> 00:13:09,520
Great, thanks for the hard work.

267
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:13,960
Try this one.

268
00:13:15,240 --> 00:13:16,120
On your end,

269
00:13:16,360 --> 00:13:17,400
once the clothes are sorted,

270
00:13:17,400 --> 00:13:18,040
head over there for the meeting.

271
00:13:18,040 --> 00:13:18,760
Sound good?

272
00:13:18,760 --> 00:13:19,400
No problem.

273
00:13:19,400 --> 00:13:20,520
Tell me if anything's off.

274
00:13:20,520 --> 00:13:21,240
Sure, sure.

275
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:24,280
One person from Factory One.

276
00:13:24,880 --> 00:13:26,760
You're doing buy-one-get-one-free?

277
00:13:27,520 --> 00:13:29,120
I'm not getting involved in this.

278
00:13:29,120 --> 00:13:30,760
I'm here to inspect the work.

279
00:13:31,560 --> 00:13:32,520
How's the preparation going?

280
00:13:32,720 --> 00:13:34,760
Lucky I built a solid base when young,

281
00:13:34,960 --> 00:13:36,360
so the craft comes back quickly.

282
00:13:36,760 --> 00:13:38,400
It's just my back that's giving out.

283
00:13:39,360 --> 00:13:40,360
Secure third, fight for second.

284
00:13:40,520 --> 00:13:41,640
Secure third, fight for second?

285
00:13:43,640 --> 00:13:44,640
That's looking iffy.

286
00:13:44,960 --> 00:13:46,120
Why iffy again?

287
00:13:46,960 --> 00:13:48,160
Jiang Erhu just stopped by.

288
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:50,520
That guy's been planning a big move.

289
00:13:51,360 --> 00:13:53,160
He's brought Jiang Yousan back.

290
00:13:54,400 --> 00:13:55,280
Jiang Yousan?

291
00:13:56,240 --> 00:13:57,400
He's back?

292
00:14:07,240 --> 00:14:08,040
Erhu.

293
00:14:08,400 --> 00:14:09,400
This old gentleman here,

294
00:14:09,400 --> 00:14:10,360
at his age,

295
00:14:10,360 --> 00:14:12,720
can still scoop with such overwhelming momentum.

296
00:14:12,720 --> 00:14:13,640
That's no easy feat.

297
00:14:13,880 --> 00:14:15,520
Don't you know who this is?

298
00:14:15,760 --> 00:14:16,760
My third uncle.

299
00:14:17,240 --> 00:14:18,400
He's the only one in the Jiang family

300
00:14:18,400 --> 00:14:20,400
who inherited the ancestral techniques.

301
00:14:20,760 --> 00:14:22,000
His skill hasn't faded a bit.

302
00:14:23,280 --> 00:14:25,120
Our Xingqiu brand Xuan paper,

303
00:14:25,120 --> 00:14:26,720
with its even cloud patterns,

304
00:14:26,840 --> 00:14:28,000
tight structure,

305
00:14:28,040 --> 00:14:29,360
and unmatched toughness,

306
00:14:30,040 --> 00:14:33,000
all comes from this overwhelming

307
00:14:33,040 --> 00:14:34,280
paper-scooping technique,

308
00:14:34,640 --> 00:14:35,760
formed by the surging water.

309
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:37,480
Whether it's Xuan Yongnian

310
00:14:37,640 --> 00:14:38,520
or anyone else,

311
00:14:38,760 --> 00:14:39,760
none can compare.

312
00:14:40,640 --> 00:14:42,880
Know yourself and your enemy to win every battle.

313
00:14:42,880 --> 00:14:45,520
So what's the Jiang family's situation now?

314
00:14:45,520 --> 00:14:48,560
It's being held up by Jiang Yousan,

315
00:14:49,280 --> 00:14:51,640
their lone star from Nanyang.

316
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:54,840
My third uncle

317
00:14:54,840 --> 00:14:56,040
usually runs the Xingqiu brand Xuan paper

318
00:14:56,040 --> 00:14:57,640
business in Southeast Asia.

319
00:14:58,000 --> 00:14:59,360
This time he's back to visit family,

320
00:14:59,480 --> 00:15:00,800
and snag the Paper King title along the way.

321
00:15:01,080 --> 00:15:02,560
If my third uncle were in China,

322
00:15:02,560 --> 00:15:03,480
this Paper King title

323
00:15:03,760 --> 00:15:05,160
would have nothing to do with the Xuan family.

324
00:15:05,640 --> 00:15:06,520
After all these years,

325
00:15:06,920 --> 00:15:09,080
the dignity the Jiang family lost

326
00:15:09,320 --> 00:15:10,280
is about to be reclaimed.

327
00:15:11,480 --> 00:15:12,880
This time is different from before,

328
00:15:13,600 --> 00:15:14,640
because Jiang Ziliu

329
00:15:15,040 --> 00:15:16,760
came over here and caused a scene.

330
00:15:16,760 --> 00:15:18,640
He said one thing at the Xuan family's place,

331
00:15:18,840 --> 00:15:20,920
that he didn't see a single sheet of good paper.

332
00:15:21,760 --> 00:15:24,000
That one remark of his

333
00:15:24,760 --> 00:15:26,560
really damaged our Xuan family's standing.

334
00:15:26,680 --> 00:15:27,520
If

335
00:15:27,920 --> 00:15:30,760
we win this competition,

336
00:15:30,840 --> 00:15:31,840
then we'll erase

337
00:15:31,840 --> 00:15:33,640
the damage Jiang Ziliu did to us.

338
00:15:33,640 --> 00:15:35,160
But if we lose,

339
00:15:35,280 --> 00:15:36,280
just you watch,

340
00:15:36,640 --> 00:15:39,240
the Xuan family will be in real trouble.

341
00:15:39,360 --> 00:15:41,240
So reputation matters more than life itself.

342
00:15:41,240 --> 00:15:42,160
Of course.

343
00:15:42,440 --> 00:15:44,640
Both reputation and life matter.

344
00:15:45,440 --> 00:15:46,680
Why do I say that?

345
00:15:47,480 --> 00:15:48,560
Because the Xuan family

346
00:15:49,960 --> 00:15:51,280
simply can't afford to lose.

347
00:15:51,400 --> 00:15:52,240
Right.

348
00:15:57,880 --> 00:15:58,560
Old Ye.

349
00:15:59,520 --> 00:16:00,280
You do it.

350
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:01,280
No.

351
00:16:03,360 --> 00:16:04,720
Don't count on me.

352
00:16:04,760 --> 00:16:06,520
I'm afraid of competitions.

353
00:16:06,760 --> 00:16:08,200
Come on, you...

354
00:16:08,720 --> 00:16:09,960
So now

355
00:16:10,840 --> 00:16:13,080
that leaves only Xuan Yan and Zhang Du.

356
00:16:14,240 --> 00:16:15,480
Zhang Du studies hard.

357
00:16:15,480 --> 00:16:16,960
His screen-lifting is steady.

358
00:16:16,960 --> 00:16:18,000
You call that steady?

359
00:16:18,120 --> 00:16:19,240
He's just copying the motions.

360
00:16:19,240 --> 00:16:20,160
He's only learned the surface.

361
00:16:20,360 --> 00:16:21,760
Three years as an apprentice,

362
00:16:21,760 --> 00:16:23,120
five and a half years to be solid,

363
00:16:23,480 --> 00:16:25,240
seven years to become a master.

364
00:16:25,240 --> 00:16:28,000
Zhang Du has only studied for a year.

365
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:28,720
He's far from ready.

366
00:16:29,480 --> 00:16:31,760
But that boy Xuan Yan,

367
00:16:31,760 --> 00:16:33,120
he's pretty sharp.

368
00:16:33,400 --> 00:16:35,240
He grew up beside the paper vat with me.

369
00:16:35,760 --> 00:16:37,960
Though he's scooped less these past few years,

370
00:16:38,360 --> 00:16:39,960
his fundamentals are still there.

371
00:16:41,120 --> 00:16:44,240
Let Xuan Yan hold the screen, Zhang Du lift it.

372
00:16:44,400 --> 00:16:45,280
That works.

373
00:16:45,760 --> 00:16:47,520
That's the best pairing.

374
00:16:47,520 --> 00:16:48,720
It's those two.

375
00:16:49,880 --> 00:16:52,120
That boy is hopeless.

376
00:16:52,360 --> 00:16:54,040
All day, every day now,

377
00:16:54,080 --> 00:16:55,240
he just fiddles with that,

378
00:16:55,360 --> 00:16:56,640
those, those, those... what's it called...

379
00:16:56,800 --> 00:16:57,880
those paper toys.

380
00:16:57,880 --> 00:16:59,000
He's obsessed with them.

381
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:00,160
Those aren't paper toys.

382
00:17:00,160 --> 00:17:02,280
They're called Xuan paper cultural products.

383
00:17:02,280 --> 00:17:03,480
I've told you a hundred times.

384
00:17:03,480 --> 00:17:04,640
You still can't remember.

385
00:17:04,640 --> 00:17:06,240
And here you go talking nonsense again.

386
00:17:06,480 --> 00:17:07,520
From ancient times to now,

387
00:17:07,520 --> 00:17:10,160
painting oils on Xuan paper,

388
00:17:10,160 --> 00:17:11,280
have you ever seen that?

389
00:17:12,280 --> 00:17:13,119
Never.

390
00:17:13,720 --> 00:17:15,240
That's a waste of Xuan paper,

391
00:17:15,280 --> 00:17:18,359
and an insult to our papermaking ancestors.

392
00:17:18,480 --> 00:17:19,160
Alright, alright.

393
00:17:19,160 --> 00:17:21,280
We're holding a meeting, why bring up ancestors?

394
00:17:22,400 --> 00:17:23,200
Xiao Yu.

395
00:17:23,200 --> 00:17:24,960
Give Xuan Yan a call.

396
00:17:25,280 --> 00:17:27,440
Tell him the whole factory is in a meeting now,

397
00:17:27,640 --> 00:17:30,280
and we've decided he'll be the screen-holder.

398
00:17:30,840 --> 00:17:31,640
Got it, Master.

399
00:17:34,120 --> 00:17:35,880
Brother Yan, where are you?

400
00:17:37,520 --> 00:17:38,240
What's up?

401
00:17:38,360 --> 00:17:39,400
There's a meeting at the factory right now.

402
00:17:39,400 --> 00:17:40,000
We're all waiting for you.

403
00:17:40,000 --> 00:17:40,960
Hurry over!

404
00:17:41,840 --> 00:17:42,240
Okay.

405
00:17:42,360 --> 00:17:43,240
Hold on.

406
00:17:43,640 --> 00:17:44,360
What are you waiting for?

407
00:17:44,360 --> 00:17:45,520
Everyone's here waiting for you.

408
00:17:45,520 --> 00:17:46,520
Just come!

409
00:17:48,840 --> 00:17:50,280
I haven't even picked up yet.

410
00:17:52,240 --> 00:17:53,320
What's that supposed to mean?

411
00:17:53,880 --> 00:17:55,240
I'm not picking up, not picking up.

412
00:17:55,240 --> 00:17:56,120
I just won't pick up.

413
00:17:57,280 --> 00:17:58,840
He's changed his ringback tone.

414
00:17:58,840 --> 00:17:59,760
You don't know anything.

415
00:18:00,760 --> 00:18:01,520
Call him, call him again.

416
00:18:01,520 --> 00:18:01,880
Keep calling.

417
00:18:01,880 --> 00:18:02,360
He hung up on me.

418
00:18:02,360 --> 00:18:02,880
Hung up.

419
00:18:03,480 --> 00:18:04,360
I'll hold the screen,

420
00:18:05,680 --> 00:18:07,280
Zhang Du lifts it.

421
00:18:07,840 --> 00:18:08,920
That's settled.

422
00:18:09,640 --> 00:18:10,280
Old Xuan.

423
00:18:10,640 --> 00:18:11,400
Old Xuan.

424
00:18:12,760 --> 00:18:13,600
Old Xuan.

425
00:18:21,120 --> 00:18:21,920
Lin Yiran.

426
00:18:23,160 --> 00:18:23,640
Come out.

427
00:18:26,720 --> 00:18:27,400
You handle it first then.

428
00:18:27,400 --> 00:18:28,160
I'll come over in a bit.

429
00:18:29,520 --> 00:18:30,520
What's going on?

430
00:18:31,040 --> 00:18:31,880
The director's angry.

431
00:18:31,880 --> 00:18:32,360
Hurry up.

432
00:18:39,960 --> 00:18:41,480
Running the Paper King Contest is work,

433
00:18:42,040 --> 00:18:43,760
but writing video channel articles isn't?

434
00:18:43,960 --> 00:18:46,040
A dozen tasks pending on the list,

435
00:18:46,040 --> 00:18:47,520
and not a soul in the office.

436
00:18:47,560 --> 00:18:49,800
Which of you has reported to me?

437
00:18:50,600 --> 00:18:51,520
Don't forget,

438
00:18:51,720 --> 00:18:52,760
I haven't retired yet.

439
00:18:52,960 --> 00:18:54,440
I'm still the Director of Economic Development.

440
00:18:54,480 --> 00:18:55,960
The contest starts tomorrow.

441
00:18:56,000 --> 00:18:57,600
So many issues are still unresolved,

442
00:18:57,600 --> 00:18:58,760
and everyone's waiting on me.

443
00:18:58,760 --> 00:19:00,800
Besides, you're not in charge of the Paper King Contest,

444
00:19:00,800 --> 00:19:02,040
so what would I report to you?

445
00:19:02,040 --> 00:19:03,320
What kind of attitude is that?

446
00:19:03,520 --> 00:19:04,520
Is that how you talk to me?

447
00:19:04,520 --> 00:19:05,760
I'm just stating the facts.

448
00:19:05,960 --> 00:19:07,280
Director Liao, Director Liao.

449
00:19:07,280 --> 00:19:08,000
What's going on?

450
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:09,280
Why such a fit of anger?

451
00:19:09,400 --> 00:19:10,200
With so many people around,

452
00:19:10,200 --> 00:19:11,760
it undermines your authority.

453
00:19:13,440 --> 00:19:15,280
Secretary Peng asked us to post

454
00:19:15,280 --> 00:19:17,800
two articles on Xuan paper makers,

455
00:19:17,800 --> 00:19:19,520
to promote the Paper King Contest.

456
00:19:19,760 --> 00:19:22,680
We need videos and interviews,

457
00:19:22,720 --> 00:19:24,240
all posted before the end of the day.

458
00:19:24,240 --> 00:19:26,200
So I can't even assign their work now?

459
00:19:26,200 --> 00:19:26,920
Lin Yiran.

460
00:19:27,520 --> 00:19:29,960
Since you're so eager to advance,

461
00:19:30,040 --> 00:19:32,280
I'll file for a transfer tomorrow,

462
00:19:32,600 --> 00:19:33,760
to make room for you.

463
00:19:37,120 --> 00:19:37,920
Director Liao.

464
00:19:38,600 --> 00:19:40,560
She even talks back to Jiang Ziliu without hesitation.

465
00:19:40,720 --> 00:19:41,160
Right?

466
00:19:41,160 --> 00:19:42,280
If you argue with her,

467
00:19:42,320 --> 00:19:43,240
it won't hurt her at all,

468
00:19:43,240 --> 00:19:44,760
it'll only damage your authority.

469
00:19:45,200 --> 00:19:47,080
You said you wanted an interview, right?

470
00:19:47,560 --> 00:19:49,920
Look, I'm a ready-made Xuan paper maker.

471
00:19:50,040 --> 00:19:51,320
Just interview me, that's all.

472
00:19:51,880 --> 00:19:53,000
Zhang Du is also here.

473
00:19:53,080 --> 00:19:54,720
He gave up his big-city job

474
00:19:54,920 --> 00:19:57,120
to come to Taohua Town as a new Xuan paper maker.

475
00:19:57,400 --> 00:19:59,240
If needed, I'll call Xiao Min over too.

476
00:20:01,040 --> 00:20:01,840
All right.

477
00:20:02,040 --> 00:20:03,240
Our Xuan family ancestors,

478
00:20:03,240 --> 00:20:04,760
over a thousand years ago,

479
00:20:04,760 --> 00:20:07,000
fled from disaster and came to Taohua Town.

480
00:20:07,080 --> 00:20:07,880
When they first arrived,

481
00:20:08,520 --> 00:20:09,520
there was no land to farm.

482
00:20:09,520 --> 00:20:11,280
They were forced deep into the mountain valleys.

483
00:20:11,600 --> 00:20:13,240
No food, no land, what to do?

484
00:20:13,520 --> 00:20:15,560
But there was plenty of green sandalwood bark on the mountains.

485
00:20:15,760 --> 00:20:17,320
They used it to make paper and trade for food.

486
00:20:17,320 --> 00:20:18,400
At the end of the day,

487
00:20:18,400 --> 00:20:20,000
it was just to put food on the table.

488
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:22,000
You can't let the whole family starve, right?

489
00:20:22,440 --> 00:20:23,680
The mountains were poor.

490
00:20:23,680 --> 00:20:24,960
There weren't even any houses.

491
00:20:25,280 --> 00:20:27,280
They'd put up a shed and start making paper.

492
00:20:27,560 --> 00:20:28,520
When the weather got hot,

493
00:20:28,520 --> 00:20:29,760
they'd just work stark naked.

494
00:20:30,560 --> 00:20:32,520
After all, there were no outsiders in those mountains.

495
00:20:33,800 --> 00:20:36,080
But word eventually got out beyond the mountains.

496
00:20:36,080 --> 00:20:37,440
The folks outside the mountains,

497
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:39,040
they looked down on us.

498
00:20:39,240 --> 00:20:40,760
They thought us papermakers

499
00:20:40,760 --> 00:20:42,000
were like wild savages.

500
00:20:42,280 --> 00:20:45,280
Later they all called us "paper beggars."

501
00:20:45,680 --> 00:20:46,320
The situation,

502
00:20:46,320 --> 00:20:47,760
well, that's just how the situation was.

503
00:20:48,080 --> 00:20:48,920
That statement of yours

504
00:20:48,920 --> 00:20:51,240
really shows off your inner world.

505
00:20:51,680 --> 00:20:52,600
Xuan Yan,

506
00:20:52,760 --> 00:20:54,240
focus on highlighting Xuan paper culture.

507
00:20:54,520 --> 00:20:56,280
Don't go rambling about random nonsense.

508
00:20:57,360 --> 00:20:58,280
In my view,

509
00:20:58,280 --> 00:21:00,960
the greatest achievement of the Xuan ancestors

510
00:21:01,360 --> 00:21:03,440
was discovering the golden ratio of

511
00:21:03,600 --> 00:21:06,760
green sandalwood bark, sandy-field rice straw, and mountain spring water.

512
00:21:07,120 --> 00:21:08,160
With endless ink variations,

513
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:10,040
it gave soul to calligraphy and painting,

514
00:21:10,320 --> 00:21:11,760
carried Chinese culture,

515
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:14,680
and inspired countless scholars throughout history.

516
00:21:14,680 --> 00:21:17,000
That's how it has been passed down to this day.

517
00:21:17,280 --> 00:21:17,840
Indeed.

518
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:18,840
Actually,

519
00:21:18,920 --> 00:21:20,160
making paper from sandalwood bark

520
00:21:20,160 --> 00:21:21,480
has been around since ancient times.

521
00:21:22,360 --> 00:21:24,280
Back then, there weren't as many sandalwood trees as today.

522
00:21:24,280 --> 00:21:26,080
Now they're cultivated on a large scale.

523
00:21:26,240 --> 00:21:28,080
What do you do when supply is short?

524
00:21:28,080 --> 00:21:29,240
This is where

525
00:21:29,240 --> 00:21:30,920
our ancestors' wisdom comes through.

526
00:21:31,200 --> 00:21:34,000
They took sandy-field rice straw and sandalwood bark,

527
00:21:34,000 --> 00:21:34,600
mixed them together,

528
00:21:34,600 --> 00:21:35,320
stirred them up,

529
00:21:35,320 --> 00:21:37,560
and unexpectedly, the result was amazing.

530
00:21:37,960 --> 00:21:40,000
I'm not saying our ancestors

531
00:21:40,040 --> 00:21:42,080
were cutting corners.

532
00:21:42,080 --> 00:21:44,480
I'm saying they knew how to adapt.

533
00:21:44,800 --> 00:21:45,520
Of course,

534
00:21:45,520 --> 00:21:46,920
it was also a makeshift solution.

535
00:21:46,920 --> 00:21:48,160
People had to eat.

536
00:21:49,080 --> 00:21:51,080
Can't let the whole family starve, right?

537
00:21:51,080 --> 00:21:51,960
Exactly.

538
00:21:52,000 --> 00:21:52,840
All right, all right.

539
00:21:52,840 --> 00:21:53,840
Stop talking.

540
00:21:54,160 --> 00:21:55,960
In the process of making Xuan paper,

541
00:21:55,960 --> 00:21:57,800
what am I really trying to express?

542
00:21:57,800 --> 00:21:59,160
What I mainly want to convey is,

543
00:21:59,840 --> 00:22:01,840
the invention of Xuan paper is indeed great,

544
00:22:02,000 --> 00:22:04,240
but there's no need to deliberately over-glorify it.

545
00:22:11,080 --> 00:22:11,920
Son.

546
00:22:12,200 --> 00:22:13,000
Mom.

547
00:22:15,320 --> 00:22:17,160
Are you throwing this stuff out

548
00:22:17,280 --> 00:22:19,040
or are you putting it away?

549
00:22:19,320 --> 00:22:20,000
This?

550
00:22:20,640 --> 00:22:22,040
I'm shipping it to Germany.

551
00:22:22,040 --> 00:22:23,640
For the Oriental Culture Exhibition.

552
00:22:25,040 --> 00:22:26,200
My son is amazing.

553
00:22:26,840 --> 00:22:28,320
Well, look whose son he is.

554
00:22:28,560 --> 00:22:29,400
Exactly.

555
00:22:29,840 --> 00:22:31,360
I'll leave the fruit on your desk.

556
00:22:32,120 --> 00:22:32,560
Okay.

557
00:22:32,560 --> 00:22:33,200
Just put it there.

558
00:22:35,960 --> 00:22:36,760
I won't lie to you,

559
00:22:38,360 --> 00:22:40,960
your dad knows he can't compete himself.

560
00:22:41,200 --> 00:22:42,640
He wants you to do it,

561
00:22:42,960 --> 00:22:44,600
but he just can't say it out loud.

562
00:22:44,640 --> 00:22:45,840
He knows the moment he asks you,

563
00:22:45,840 --> 00:22:47,200
you'll definitely refuse.

564
00:22:48,160 --> 00:22:49,760
So he racked his brains,

565
00:22:49,800 --> 00:22:52,240
beating around the bush with that meeting.

566
00:22:52,680 --> 00:22:53,600
You know what?

567
00:22:53,920 --> 00:22:55,240
After that meeting ended,

568
00:22:55,240 --> 00:22:57,520
my heart was just pounding.

569
00:22:57,920 --> 00:22:58,520
Son,

570
00:22:58,960 --> 00:23:00,160
today it's just us two,

571
00:23:00,160 --> 00:23:02,240
and I'm having a heart-to-heart with you.

572
00:23:02,520 --> 00:23:03,800
Your dad's back...

573
00:23:03,960 --> 00:23:05,240
If he goes and competes,

574
00:23:05,400 --> 00:23:07,680
what if it gives out, breaks?

575
00:23:08,120 --> 00:23:09,120
Or even worse,

576
00:23:09,120 --> 00:23:09,920
paralyzed.

577
00:23:10,480 --> 00:23:12,400
How would our family get by then?

578
00:23:12,680 --> 00:23:14,200
What would he do for the rest of his life?

579
00:23:14,200 --> 00:23:15,480
Have you thought about that?

580
00:23:15,760 --> 00:23:17,440
He even wants me to be his successor.

581
00:23:17,440 --> 00:23:18,240
And I already agreed.

582
00:23:18,240 --> 00:23:19,200
Of course you had to agree.

583
00:23:19,200 --> 00:23:20,600
You're the only son in this family.

584
00:23:20,600 --> 00:23:22,040
If not you, then who?

585
00:23:22,040 --> 00:23:23,400
He can pass it to whoever he wants.

586
00:23:42,040 --> 00:23:42,840
Master.

587
00:23:44,120 --> 00:23:44,720
Master.

588
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:46,040
Your back's acting up again.

589
00:23:46,840 --> 00:23:47,520
Come here.

590
00:23:48,040 --> 00:23:49,240
I told you not to do it.

591
00:23:49,240 --> 00:23:50,560
You just had to push yourself.

592
00:23:52,000 --> 00:23:52,800
Master.

593
00:23:52,960 --> 00:23:54,240
You should stop working.

594
00:23:54,680 --> 00:23:56,000
I'll take this material down.

595
00:23:56,000 --> 00:23:56,680
I'll handle it.

596
00:24:02,080 --> 00:24:02,880
You rest now.

597
00:24:02,880 --> 00:24:03,680
Wait till I get back.

598
00:24:11,640 --> 00:24:14,280
If my son were half as good as Zhang Du,

599
00:24:16,040 --> 00:24:17,760
I'd be content.

600
00:24:20,560 --> 00:24:21,960
What you are at three,

601
00:24:22,520 --> 00:24:23,720
you'll be at seventy.

602
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:25,560
That boy Xuan Yan,

603
00:24:26,160 --> 00:24:28,000
he's kind and honest.

604
00:24:28,480 --> 00:24:29,560
He won't go off the rails.

605
00:24:30,240 --> 00:24:31,520
No need to worry about him.

606
00:24:31,840 --> 00:24:33,520
If I had a son like him,

607
00:24:34,440 --> 00:24:36,400
I'd laugh in my sleep.

608
00:24:41,800 --> 00:24:42,720
Xuan Yan.

609
00:24:43,240 --> 00:24:44,720
Tell me, this Xuan paper,

610
00:24:44,720 --> 00:24:46,880
does it really have no future?

611
00:24:49,520 --> 00:24:50,960
Back when I was in college,

612
00:24:51,320 --> 00:24:52,840
I asked my classmates.

613
00:24:52,840 --> 00:24:54,360
I said, "Do you know Xuan paper?"

614
00:24:54,720 --> 00:24:56,000
Most of them did.

615
00:24:56,440 --> 00:24:57,240
Then I asked,

616
00:24:57,240 --> 00:24:58,960
"Would you ever buy Xuan paper?"

617
00:24:59,400 --> 00:25:00,240
They said,

618
00:25:00,760 --> 00:25:02,760
"I don't need it, why would I buy it?"

619
00:25:03,040 --> 00:25:04,760
That's the reality.

620
00:25:05,400 --> 00:25:07,440
The Xuan paper we treasure,

621
00:25:07,800 --> 00:25:09,280
to people who don't need it,

622
00:25:09,280 --> 00:25:11,480
it's just an ordinary sheet of paper.

623
00:25:12,160 --> 00:25:13,560
What I'm doing now

624
00:25:13,760 --> 00:25:15,520
is to give Xuan paper

625
00:25:15,520 --> 00:25:17,160
a new way forward.

626
00:25:17,800 --> 00:25:19,040
I want it

627
00:25:19,120 --> 00:25:21,920
to enter more people's everyday lives.

628
00:25:22,320 --> 00:25:25,040
From basic use to understanding,

629
00:25:25,200 --> 00:25:28,040
we build up a new customer base.

630
00:25:28,160 --> 00:25:30,160
Only then can traditional Xuan paper

631
00:25:30,600 --> 00:25:32,800
show its higher value.

632
00:25:34,880 --> 00:25:37,880
Look how great your ideas and vision are.

633
00:25:37,880 --> 00:25:39,600
Why don't you talk to your dad?

634
00:25:39,600 --> 00:25:40,880
So he'll stop saying all day

635
00:25:40,880 --> 00:25:42,480
that you're taking his fine Xuan paper

636
00:25:42,480 --> 00:25:43,520
and messing around with it,

637
00:25:43,520 --> 00:25:44,280
wasting it.

638
00:25:44,520 --> 00:25:46,520
Can I even talk to him?

639
00:25:46,520 --> 00:25:47,240
Then I'll tell him.

640
00:25:47,240 --> 00:25:47,760
No, no, no.

641
00:25:47,760 --> 00:25:48,560
Don't you go either.

642
00:25:48,560 --> 00:25:49,560
With his temper,

643
00:25:49,560 --> 00:25:50,560
that stubbornness of his,

644
00:25:50,560 --> 00:25:51,320
once he gets going,

645
00:25:51,480 --> 00:25:53,320
tradition, ancestors...

646
00:25:53,560 --> 00:25:54,600
even you can't talk sense into him.

647
00:25:54,680 --> 00:25:55,560
Besides,

648
00:25:55,560 --> 00:25:56,520
my dad and I

649
00:25:56,800 --> 00:25:58,760
have two principles for peace.

650
00:25:59,400 --> 00:26:01,240
I don't provoke him,

651
00:26:01,240 --> 00:26:02,320
and he doesn't provoke me.

652
00:26:02,320 --> 00:26:04,000
The status quo works just fine.

653
00:26:05,760 --> 00:26:06,200
Fine.

654
00:26:07,080 --> 00:26:08,840
Anyway, you know what I mean.

655
00:26:10,040 --> 00:26:12,160
Your dad can't go to the competition.

656
00:26:12,400 --> 00:26:13,520
Just so you understand.

657
00:26:15,240 --> 00:26:16,040
Mom.

658
00:26:17,200 --> 00:26:18,480
I almost forgot.

659
00:26:20,880 --> 00:26:23,200
My classmate from Inner Mongolia recommended this.

660
00:26:23,320 --> 00:26:25,120
Said it's good for herniated discs.

661
00:26:25,320 --> 00:26:26,360
Put it on Dad for me.

662
00:26:26,920 --> 00:26:27,720
Look at this.

663
00:26:28,760 --> 00:26:29,520
Just look.

664
00:26:30,560 --> 00:26:32,880
You care about your dad the most.

665
00:26:33,760 --> 00:26:35,160
And the one who cares about me most

666
00:26:35,920 --> 00:26:37,040
is my mom.

667
00:26:38,000 --> 00:26:39,240
As long as you know it in your heart.

668
00:26:39,760 --> 00:26:41,520
Keep what I said in mind.

669
00:26:41,520 --> 00:26:42,600
Got it, Mom.

670
00:26:46,000 --> 00:26:46,840
It's delicious, Mom.

671
00:26:53,160 --> 00:26:54,520
Not too hot, just right.

672
00:26:54,800 --> 00:26:55,760
Just right.

673
00:26:59,160 --> 00:27:00,560
Look at that.

674
00:27:01,600 --> 00:27:03,080
Who cares about you the most?

675
00:27:03,400 --> 00:27:04,760
Only your son.

676
00:27:06,880 --> 00:27:08,400
If he'd listen to me,

677
00:27:09,040 --> 00:27:10,560
and stop sulking at me,

678
00:27:11,080 --> 00:27:12,960
I'd be content for life.

679
00:27:13,040 --> 00:27:14,280
Listen to you?

680
00:27:14,800 --> 00:27:16,200
My son is better than you.

681
00:27:16,200 --> 00:27:17,600
Why should he listen to you?

682
00:27:20,680 --> 00:27:21,400
All right.

683
00:27:21,480 --> 00:27:22,280
Get up.

684
00:27:22,560 --> 00:27:24,160
Try the back brace I bought you.

685
00:27:30,880 --> 00:27:31,480
Come on.

686
00:27:40,760 --> 00:27:41,600
Let's go take a look.

687
00:27:48,200 --> 00:27:49,000
Yongnian.

688
00:27:49,760 --> 00:27:51,840
Think about how old you are.

689
00:27:52,240 --> 00:27:53,840
Competing against those young guys,

690
00:27:53,840 --> 00:27:55,200
how could you possibly win?

691
00:27:55,920 --> 00:27:57,560
This time, I'm begging you.

692
00:27:57,760 --> 00:27:59,520
Let's just skip it, okay?

693
00:28:00,640 --> 00:28:02,760
We don't need that Paper King title.

694
00:28:03,840 --> 00:28:05,480
This back support of yours is really nice.

695
00:28:05,480 --> 00:28:06,120
Look at this.

696
00:28:06,120 --> 00:28:07,600
I can straighten my back now.

697
00:28:07,600 --> 00:28:08,080
See?

698
00:28:08,720 --> 00:28:09,480
Full of strength.

699
00:28:11,840 --> 00:28:12,560
Let me tell you,

700
00:28:12,560 --> 00:28:14,520
I'm definitely entering this contest.

701
00:28:14,880 --> 00:28:15,880
I, Xuan Yongnian,

702
00:28:15,960 --> 00:28:17,200
apart from making paper,

703
00:28:17,200 --> 00:28:18,560
have no other skills.

704
00:28:18,600 --> 00:28:21,240
But this Paper King Contest,

705
00:28:21,440 --> 00:28:22,520
I can't afford to lose.

706
00:28:22,520 --> 00:28:23,440
If I lose,

707
00:28:23,440 --> 00:28:25,360
wouldn't that be utterly humiliating?

708
00:28:25,920 --> 00:28:27,760
This year's Paper King Contest

709
00:28:28,080 --> 00:28:32,040
has invited several distinguished judges.

710
00:28:32,360 --> 00:28:33,600
They are as follows:

711
00:28:33,600 --> 00:28:36,040
National-level Master of Arts and Crafts,

712
00:28:36,520 --> 00:28:37,960
Mr. Shen Guojun.

713
00:28:42,320 --> 00:28:45,320
Chief Engineer of Hongxing Xuan Paper Co.,

714
00:28:45,800 --> 00:28:48,440
National Intangible Cultural Heritage Inheritor,

715
00:28:48,680 --> 00:28:50,440
Master Man Chenggui.

716
00:28:51,400 --> 00:28:55,240
Chief expert of the Provincial Museum's Painting and Calligraphy Hall,

717
00:28:55,400 --> 00:28:56,920
Professor Qian Cong.

718
00:28:57,800 --> 00:28:59,760
Representative of Dayazhai Cultural Group,

719
00:28:59,760 --> 00:29:02,880
General Manager of Dayazhai's Taohua Town branch,

720
00:29:02,880 --> 00:29:04,200
Ms. Xin Ran.

721
00:29:14,280 --> 00:29:17,680
This Paper King Contest is divided into four judging rounds.

722
00:29:18,160 --> 00:29:21,160
They are: paper-scooping speed race,

723
00:29:21,680 --> 00:29:22,680
finished-product rate,

724
00:29:23,280 --> 00:29:24,600
specified weight standard,

725
00:29:25,000 --> 00:29:26,360
and expert brush test.

726
00:29:27,280 --> 00:29:30,000
Each round has a maximum of five points,

727
00:29:30,400 --> 00:29:32,280
and a minimum of one point.

728
00:29:33,240 --> 00:29:36,200
Those who fail to finish receive zero points.

729
00:29:36,760 --> 00:29:37,480
Now,

730
00:29:37,840 --> 00:29:40,640
we begin the first round of the contest:

731
00:29:40,640 --> 00:29:42,320
the paper-scooping speed race.

732
00:29:42,480 --> 00:29:43,680
The rules are as follows:

733
00:29:44,240 --> 00:29:46,760
Within one hour,

734
00:29:46,760 --> 00:29:49,320
whoever produces the most sheets wins.

735
00:29:49,760 --> 00:29:51,280
Yongnian's back is in bad shape.

736
00:29:51,280 --> 00:29:52,240
I hereby declare

737
00:29:52,760 --> 00:29:54,160
the paper-scooping contest

738
00:29:54,520 --> 00:29:56,040
officially begun.

739
00:30:04,320 --> 00:30:05,600
Don't be nervous. Take it steady.

740
00:30:10,800 --> 00:30:12,000
Two people scoop paper together.

741
00:30:12,760 --> 00:30:13,920
The lead screen-holder is in charge.

742
00:30:14,400 --> 00:30:16,520
The mantra is: front hand must be firm.

743
00:30:17,000 --> 00:30:19,160
Thickness depends entirely on feel.

744
00:30:19,280 --> 00:30:21,760
Controlling the weight and evenness of the paper.

745
00:30:21,960 --> 00:30:26,560
The lift-screen mantra: back hand loose, flow with the movement.

746
00:30:26,760 --> 00:30:28,080
First scoop draws water toward you,

747
00:30:28,320 --> 00:30:31,320
meaning dip deep and lay the base evenly.

748
00:30:31,600 --> 00:30:33,200
Second scoop breaks through the center.

749
00:30:33,200 --> 00:30:35,120
Through two layers of water overlapping,

750
00:30:35,240 --> 00:30:37,840
the pulp fibers interlock together,

751
00:30:38,240 --> 00:30:39,600
filling the center and leveling out,

752
00:30:40,000 --> 00:30:43,920
ultimately controlling the paper's toughness and evenness.

753
00:30:58,000 --> 00:30:59,480
The Jiang family from Nanyang

754
00:30:59,480 --> 00:31:01,040
has truly exceptional scooping skills.

755
00:31:02,080 --> 00:31:02,920
Impressive.

756
00:31:03,320 --> 00:31:05,200
To carve out a name in Nanyang,

757
00:31:05,520 --> 00:31:07,000
they really do have a masterful touch.

758
00:31:07,440 --> 00:31:08,960
But to win this contest,

759
00:31:10,240 --> 00:31:13,160
it still depends on whether Xuan Yongnian agrees.

760
00:31:32,000 --> 00:31:33,320
Master, your back...

761
00:31:46,000 --> 00:31:46,800
What about it?

762
00:31:47,040 --> 00:31:48,480
Did you see that Jiang guy?

763
00:31:48,720 --> 00:31:49,840
He's really impressive.

764
00:31:50,280 --> 00:31:51,960
They say he's the Xuan family's biggest rival.

765
00:31:52,600 --> 00:31:54,240
And I noticed Uncle Xuan's back

766
00:31:54,760 --> 00:31:55,760
seems a bit off too.

767
00:31:56,800 --> 00:31:58,000
Auntie Xu mentioned

768
00:31:58,000 --> 00:31:58,760
that Uncle Xuan's

769
00:31:58,760 --> 00:32:00,720
herniated disc has flared up again lately.

770
00:32:00,720 --> 00:32:01,920
And it's gotten worse.

771
00:32:03,080 --> 00:32:03,920
We're done for.

772
00:32:04,520 --> 00:32:05,920
Then we're probably really finished.

773
00:32:06,320 --> 00:32:08,240
Look how many media outlets came today.

774
00:32:08,400 --> 00:32:09,320
They're saying if the championship

775
00:32:09,320 --> 00:32:10,920
goes to someone outside Taohua Town,

776
00:32:11,520 --> 00:32:12,760
it'll really prove that Taohua Town

777
00:32:12,760 --> 00:32:14,000
can no longer make good paper.

778
00:32:16,680 --> 00:32:17,800
It's too late to say anything now.

779
00:32:18,240 --> 00:32:19,120
Let's just leave it to fate.

780
00:32:20,040 --> 00:32:21,200
Alright, hurry along now.

781
00:32:23,120 --> 00:32:23,760
Excuse me, coming through.

782
00:32:23,760 --> 00:32:24,640
Thanks, thanks.

783
00:32:42,480 --> 00:32:43,680
I've been counting, you know.

784
00:32:44,240 --> 00:32:45,120
My third uncle

785
00:32:45,120 --> 00:32:46,240
beat Xuan Yongnian

786
00:32:46,560 --> 00:32:47,440
by more than a dozen sheets.

787
00:32:49,680 --> 00:32:51,240
I really didn't expect it.

788
00:32:51,320 --> 00:32:53,320
Your third uncle's really impressive.

789
00:32:53,600 --> 00:32:54,960
In all of Southeast Asia,

790
00:32:55,200 --> 00:32:56,200
he's number one.

791
00:32:56,520 --> 00:32:57,440
What did you think?

792
00:33:04,120 --> 00:33:04,560
Master.

793
00:33:04,560 --> 00:33:05,480
Master, your back can't take it anymore.

794
00:33:06,160 --> 00:33:06,600
Master.

795
00:33:08,400 --> 00:33:09,280
I'm fine.

796
00:33:10,000 --> 00:33:11,400
Don't get nervous. Take it steady.

797
00:33:12,800 --> 00:33:13,720
Old Xuan's got this.

798
00:33:44,440 --> 00:33:45,240
Master.

799
00:33:45,240 --> 00:33:46,320
Is the glare bothering you?

800
00:33:46,560 --> 00:33:47,520
It's really annoying.

801
00:33:48,720 --> 00:33:49,520
Judges.

802
00:33:51,600 --> 00:33:52,200
What is it?

803
00:33:52,200 --> 00:33:52,920
Officials,

804
00:33:53,400 --> 00:33:55,000
could you switch us to another vat?

805
00:33:55,040 --> 00:33:56,600
The glare here is too harsh.

806
00:33:58,840 --> 00:34:00,520
There aren't any spare vats left.

807
00:34:00,600 --> 00:34:02,160
Come on, that's not fair.

808
00:34:05,960 --> 00:34:06,520
Zhang Du.

809
00:34:06,520 --> 00:34:07,000
Yes?

810
00:34:07,000 --> 00:34:07,720
Come here.

811
00:34:08,239 --> 00:34:08,920
Master.

812
00:34:08,920 --> 00:34:09,639
Hurry up.

813
00:34:12,000 --> 00:34:13,520
Master, can we really do this blind?

814
00:34:13,520 --> 00:34:14,520
Think of it as a night shift.

815
00:34:14,520 --> 00:34:15,719
We work at night just the same, don't we?

816
00:34:15,719 --> 00:34:16,440
Hurry up.

817
00:34:16,800 --> 00:34:18,080
Quick, we're running out of time.

818
00:34:18,520 --> 00:34:19,120
Okay.

819
00:34:22,679 --> 00:34:25,400
What's old man Xuan up to now?

820
00:34:25,600 --> 00:34:27,159
Why has he blindfolded himself?

821
00:34:29,320 --> 00:34:30,199
Sister Xiumei,

822
00:34:30,760 --> 00:34:32,600
can he really do it blindfolded?

823
00:35:56,800 --> 00:35:57,520
Nice, nice, nice!

824
00:35:57,520 --> 00:35:58,600
Master, you got this!

825
00:35:58,800 --> 00:35:59,680
Come on, Master!

826
00:36:00,600 --> 00:36:01,720
Go, Yongnian!

827
00:36:04,720 --> 00:36:05,560
Impressive!

828
00:36:05,640 --> 00:36:07,200
Old Xuan's still got it!

829
00:36:07,640 --> 00:36:08,720
Still sharp as ever.

830
00:36:09,560 --> 00:36:10,560
All contestants...

831
00:36:11,520 --> 00:36:12,360
Keep it up!

832
00:36:21,400 --> 00:36:23,520
Yongnian's strain is mostly on his back.

833
00:36:23,720 --> 00:36:25,320
I'm just afraid he can't hold out.

834
00:36:52,560 --> 00:36:54,360
Ten seconds left!

835
00:36:54,880 --> 00:36:55,680
Come on!

836
00:37:05,440 --> 00:37:06,480
Time's up!

837
00:37:06,480 --> 00:37:07,800
Stop!

838
00:37:08,320 --> 00:37:09,080
Halt!

839
00:37:09,720 --> 00:37:10,360
Come on, let's go check it out.

840
00:37:10,360 --> 00:37:10,920
The competition is over.

841
00:37:10,920 --> 00:37:11,520
Master!

842
00:37:15,560 --> 00:37:18,520
All counters, please report to the organizing team.

843
00:37:18,520 --> 00:37:19,280
Master!

844
00:37:19,520 --> 00:37:20,480
Are you okay, Master?

845
00:37:23,080 --> 00:37:23,800
Master! Master!

846
00:37:24,280 --> 00:37:24,560
Master!

847
00:37:24,560 --> 00:37:25,000
Hurry, hurry!

848
00:37:25,000 --> 00:37:25,920
A chair, get a chair!

849
00:37:25,920 --> 00:37:26,520
Hurry up!

850
00:37:26,520 --> 00:37:27,280
Sit down, sit down.

851
00:37:27,440 --> 00:37:28,040
Yongnian.

852
00:37:28,040 --> 00:37:29,000
Take it easy, Master.

853
00:37:29,000 --> 00:37:30,000
Slow down, slow down.

854
00:37:30,440 --> 00:37:31,360
Easy, Master.

855
00:37:31,680 --> 00:37:32,320
Slowly.

856
00:37:33,440 --> 00:37:34,120
Have some water.

857
00:37:34,120 --> 00:37:34,760
Yongnian.

858
00:37:34,760 --> 00:37:35,400
Are you all right?

859
00:37:36,120 --> 00:37:37,360
How's your back holding up?

860
00:37:41,160 --> 00:37:42,440
Easy, easy, easy.

861
00:37:42,560 --> 00:37:43,520
Take it slow, Master.

862
00:37:45,280 --> 00:37:46,160
How's your back?

863
00:37:51,280 --> 00:37:52,080
Let's go.

864
00:37:54,320 --> 00:37:55,280
Go check on the old man.

865
00:38:03,640 --> 00:38:04,880
Sorry to keep you all waiting.

866
00:38:07,000 --> 00:38:10,280
After verification by the counters,

867
00:38:10,880 --> 00:38:12,520
and confirmation with the contestants,

868
00:38:12,840 --> 00:38:15,600
the paper-scooping counts are as follows:

869
00:38:16,680 --> 00:38:17,960
Xingqiu Paper Industry,

870
00:38:18,440 --> 00:38:21,920
184 sheets, scoring 5 points.

871
00:38:23,320 --> 00:38:24,600
Third Uncle, amazing!

872
00:38:24,600 --> 00:38:25,840
Huihuang Paper Industry,

873
00:38:26,360 --> 00:38:28,080
181 sheets,

874
00:38:28,920 --> 00:38:29,840
scoring 4 points.

875
00:38:31,120 --> 00:38:33,120
Xuan Family Paper Mill, one hundred...

876
00:38:33,640 --> 00:38:36,080
172 sheets, scoring 3 points.

877
00:38:37,800 --> 00:38:39,120
Qunxing Paper Mill,

878
00:38:40,040 --> 00:38:42,480
165 sheets, scoring 2 points.

879
00:38:43,960 --> 00:38:45,200
Jinxuan Paper Mill,

880
00:38:45,560 --> 00:38:48,080
147 sheets, scoring 1 point.

881
00:38:49,840 --> 00:38:52,080
The contest was fair, the data accurate.

882
00:38:52,720 --> 00:38:53,600
I hereby announce:

883
00:38:54,200 --> 00:38:56,920
For round one, the paper-scooping speed contest,

884
00:38:57,000 --> 00:38:58,720
Xingqiu Paper Industry is the winner!

885
00:38:58,800 --> 00:38:59,560
Yes!

886
00:39:00,080 --> 00:39:01,000
Thank you, everyone.

887
00:39:01,720 --> 00:39:02,640
Thank you all.

888
00:39:10,360 --> 00:39:12,080
Uncle, congratulations!

889
00:39:31,320 --> 00:39:33,760
We worked so hard to put on this big contest.

890
00:39:35,280 --> 00:39:35,920
And now it looks like

891
00:39:37,720 --> 00:39:40,600
we've made a fool of Taohua Town.

892
00:39:48,920 --> 00:39:49,720
Old Xuan.

893
00:39:50,240 --> 00:39:52,240
This whole thing is mainly my fault.

894
00:39:52,400 --> 00:39:54,440
If I hadn't been so nervous about competing,

895
00:39:54,440 --> 00:39:55,760
I would've gone up there myself.

896
00:39:55,760 --> 00:39:57,000
Look at the mess we're in.

897
00:39:57,920 --> 00:39:59,000
It's not your fault.

898
00:39:59,120 --> 00:40:00,120
If anyone's to blame,

899
00:40:00,680 --> 00:40:02,880
it's this useless back of mine.

900
00:40:03,720 --> 00:40:04,520
Master.

901
00:40:05,320 --> 00:40:07,120
If you ask me, no one's to blame.

902
00:40:07,240 --> 00:40:08,680
Blame it on the sun.

903
00:40:08,680 --> 00:40:10,400
Right during the contest, of all times,

904
00:40:10,400 --> 00:40:12,280
it had to shine right into Master's eyes.

905
00:40:12,680 --> 00:40:14,000
That's what threw Master off.

906
00:40:14,760 --> 00:40:17,440
It's only day one, no need to worry.

907
00:40:17,440 --> 00:40:18,080
Right.

908
00:40:18,160 --> 00:40:19,280
I'll handle the paper drying.

909
00:40:19,320 --> 00:40:20,880
It's just a contest of finished-product rate.

910
00:40:20,880 --> 00:40:21,880
I guarantee you,

911
00:40:21,920 --> 00:40:23,960
a hundred sheets, not a single flaw.

912
00:40:24,560 --> 00:40:25,840
That's what I'm saying too.

913
00:40:25,880 --> 00:40:28,400
We can't lose the weighing contest either.

914
00:40:28,680 --> 00:40:29,440
By the rules,

915
00:40:29,440 --> 00:40:30,680
six and a half jin per stack.

916
00:40:30,840 --> 00:40:32,040
With Old Xuan's craftsmanship,

917
00:40:32,040 --> 00:40:33,280
the difference won't even be five qian.

918
00:40:33,280 --> 00:40:33,680
Exactly.

919
00:40:33,680 --> 00:40:34,440
Right.

920
00:40:34,960 --> 00:40:36,080
Let the experts judge.

921
00:40:36,080 --> 00:40:37,080
When it comes to quality,

922
00:40:37,080 --> 00:40:39,080
no one better than my master has been born yet.

923
00:40:39,080 --> 00:40:39,800
Right?

924
00:40:41,160 --> 00:40:42,320
Don't say such things.

925
00:40:42,520 --> 00:40:43,200
I know.

926
00:40:43,200 --> 00:40:45,200
Master, we're just talking among ourselves.

927
00:40:45,200 --> 00:40:46,840
Even behind closed doors, don't say it.

928
00:40:46,840 --> 00:40:47,680
Master Xuan.

929
00:40:48,000 --> 00:40:49,720
I'll pair up with Lao Ke for drying paper.

930
00:40:50,680 --> 00:40:51,640
What's that supposed to mean?

931
00:40:51,640 --> 00:40:53,880
Your husband's right here and you pick Lao Ke?

932
00:40:54,160 --> 00:40:55,160
Let's pair up together.

933
00:40:55,160 --> 00:40:56,480
Who wants to pair up with you?

934
00:40:56,520 --> 00:40:57,840
You never understand a thing I say.

935
00:40:57,840 --> 00:40:59,520
All you do is make people angry.

936
00:40:59,640 --> 00:41:00,480
Look at you.

937
00:41:09,280 --> 00:41:10,080
Contestants.

938
00:41:10,560 --> 00:41:11,720
Let me remind you once again,

939
00:41:12,240 --> 00:41:13,280
within one hour,

940
00:41:13,560 --> 00:41:15,080
the winner is decided by finished-product rate.

941
00:41:15,400 --> 00:41:17,280
Anyone below 90 percent

942
00:41:17,280 --> 00:41:18,280
will be considered disqualified.

943
00:41:18,320 --> 00:41:20,040
Good luck, contestants.

944
00:41:20,440 --> 00:41:21,400
Do your best.

945
00:41:21,880 --> 00:41:22,640
Come on.

946
00:41:26,360 --> 00:41:26,880
Look.

947
00:41:27,160 --> 00:41:28,640
Something's wrong with this paper, Lao Ke.

948
00:41:32,760 --> 00:41:33,560
Look.

949
00:41:35,000 --> 00:41:35,800
Don't rush.

950
00:41:35,800 --> 00:41:36,560
Let it soak a bit more.

951
00:41:37,520 --> 00:41:38,320
Come on.

952
00:41:42,800 --> 00:41:43,480
Look at that.

953
00:41:43,480 --> 00:41:44,480
One pull and several sheets come off.

954
00:41:46,280 --> 00:41:46,840
What's wrong?

955
00:41:51,000 --> 00:41:51,800
What happened?

956
00:41:52,400 --> 00:41:53,120
We've got a problem here.

957
00:41:53,120 --> 00:41:54,120
Something's wrong with this paper.

958
00:41:54,200 --> 00:41:55,280
Here, let me try.

959
00:42:02,360 --> 00:42:03,800
Look.

960
00:42:04,160 --> 00:42:05,280
It won't peel apart.

961
00:42:05,320 --> 00:42:06,400
And it won't go up either.

962
00:42:06,880 --> 00:42:07,960
Hurry, tell Yongnian.

963
00:42:08,040 --> 00:42:09,000
I'll go find our factory manager.

964
00:42:09,000 --> 00:42:09,760
Go quickly.

965
00:42:10,320 --> 00:42:10,600
Thank you.

966
00:42:10,600 --> 00:42:11,160
Go with him.

967
00:42:11,160 --> 00:42:11,920
Thank you.

968
00:42:12,600 --> 00:42:13,440
Master Xuan.

969
00:42:15,080 --> 00:42:15,800
Master Xuan.

970
00:42:15,800 --> 00:42:16,520
Open it.

971
00:42:18,720 --> 00:42:20,200
Hurry, come in and take a look.

972
00:42:20,280 --> 00:42:21,080
What's going on?

973
00:42:21,680 --> 00:42:22,520
Let's go.

974
00:42:22,520 --> 00:42:23,120
Mrs. Xuan.

975
00:42:23,120 --> 00:42:23,920
Go quickly.

976
00:42:25,200 --> 00:42:26,320
What on earth happened?

977
00:42:26,320 --> 00:42:27,960
No idea, but something must've gone wrong.

978
00:42:28,280 --> 00:42:29,040
Don't worry.

979
00:42:29,200 --> 00:42:30,480
Old Xuan's gone in.

980
00:42:48,120 --> 00:42:48,880
Where's the spray bottle?

981
00:42:49,040 --> 00:42:49,480
Right here.

982
00:42:49,480 --> 00:42:50,200
Here it is.

983
00:42:56,960 --> 00:42:57,920
This smell isn't right.
